{"id":801496611,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"6 months, 1 week","timestamp":1663355095,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"16 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/801496611/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"8.3 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int romanToInt(string s) {\n        ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);\n        cin.tie(0), cout.tie(0);\n        \n        map<char,int> mp;\n        mp['I']=1;\n        mp['V'] = 5; mp['X'] = 10;\n        mp['L'] = 50; mp['C'] = 100;\n        mp['D'] = 500; mp['M'] = 1000;\n        \n        bool isTaken = false;\n        int ans = 0, n = s.size();\n        char ch,ch2;\n        \n        for(int i=0;i<n-1;){\n            ch = s[i];\n            ch2 = s[i+1];\n            if( mp[ch] < mp[ch2] ){\n                ans += mp[ch2]-mp[ch];\n                i+=2;\n                if(i==n) isTaken = true;\n            }\n            else{\n                i++;\n                ans += mp[ch];\n            }\n            \n        }\n        if(!isTaken) ans+=mp[s[s.size()-1]];\n        return ans;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false}
